I'm wondering why it was necessary to change the word store to scheme? I think store better represents what the thing is... it is a storage driver.

Patch Set 2:

The default_store variable is really a scheme, not a store class, the schemes are provided by the stores so it seems more relevant to name the function as verify a scheme which itself is connected to a store. I can rename that conf variable if we want, but that might have other side-effects.

Patch Set 8: No score

I saw you asking about this in IRC, so I'll tell you how I go about debugging 'Unexpected server launch status':

 1) rm -fr /tmp/test.*; ./run_tests.sh <failing_test_method>
 2) source .venv/bin/activate
 3) ./bin/glance-api --config_file=/tmp/test.<random_number>/etc/api.conf

Using that approach, I found this traceback -> http://paste.openstack.org/show/16879/
